SIMPLE: annihilate
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Annihilate
<hw>An*ni"hi*late</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Annihilated</conjf>; <pos>p. pr.
& vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Annihilating</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L.
<ets>annihilare</ets>; <ets>ad</ets> + <ets>nihilum</ets>,
<ets>nihil</ets>, nothing, <ets>ne hilum</ets> (<ets>filum</ets>) not a
thread, nothing at all. Cf. <er>File</er>, a row.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>To reduce to nothing or nonexistence; to destroy the existence of;
to cause to cease to be.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It impossible for any body to be utterly
<qex>annihilated</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To destroy the form or peculiar distinctive
properties of, so that the specific thing no longer exists; <as>as, to
<ex>annihilate</ex> a forest by cutting down the trees</as>.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧To <xex>annihilate</xex> the army.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Macaulay.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To destroy or eradicate, as a property or attribute
of a thing; to make of no effect; to destroy the force, etc., of;
<as>as, to <ex>annihilate</ex> an argument, law, rights,
goodness</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Annihilate</ent>⟦br⟧

